By James Sowole in Akure The Ondo State Government has approved the reopening of schools for all classes in public and private schools across the state beginning from Monday The State Commissioner for Education, Mr Femi Agagu, disclosed the directive of Governor Oluwarotimi Akeredolu in a statement. He said the directive for the resumption of schools was sequel to the fact that the state had become peaceful. He enjoined parents and the public to note the directive adding that all schools are to comply.